    "description": "The strategy is a long only tactical allocation to US large cap equities via SPY that seeks to participate in sustained equity upside while enforcing a hard portfolio level drawdown limit. The core signal is a trailing peak to trough risk trigger: the system remains fully invested in SPY under normal conditions and exits to cash when the total portfolio value falls more than 4 percent from the most recent observed level, aiming to cut exposure during abrupt adverse moves and reduce sequence of r",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a long only tactical allocation to US large cap equities via SPY that seeks to participate in sustained equity upside while enforcing a hard portfolio level drawdown limit. The core signal is a trailing peak to trough risk trigger: the system remains fully invested in SPY under normal conditions and exits to cash when the total portfolio value falls more than 4 percent from the most recent observed level, aiming to cut exposure during abrupt adverse moves and reduce sequence of returns risk.\n\nDecisions are made on daily data. Entry occurs only when the portfolio is in cash and at least 30 calendar days have elapsed since the last forced liquidation, creating a cooldown that avoids immediate re entry after a loss event. Exit occurs via full liquidation when the portfolio value breaches the 4 percent drawdown threshold while invested. Position sizing is binary (100 percent SPY or 0 percent), with risk control driven entirely by the drawdown stop and the 30 day re entry delay; there is no leverage, diversification, or volatility targeting. The intended edge is behavioral or crash sensitivity mitigation through fast de risking after equity drawdowns.",
